{"_id":"f8d8955e-80ac-3922-b758-b6cd3f92ca2f","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"28dde5772b48c92e08b8050411aa5ba8","message":"Yes. Reflection-based platforms such as ASP.NET WebAPI/MVC, MSTest, etc, all determine the asynchrony of a method by its return type. A method returning \"string\" must be synchronous, and a method returning \"Task<string>\" is assumed to follow the Task-based Asynchronous Pattern, and treated as asynchronous.","postId":"2012_07_dont-block-on-async-code-abe2d9c7-c3e9-3ed8-827c-021686fa2310","replyTo":"dc859b04-1355-3cf5-9b1a-7c779f5b3431","date":"2015-02-18T17:39:53Z","timestamp":1424281193,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}